quran[26]{c,v,t,f}:
  75,20,"No indeed! You [people] love this fleeting world,",""
  75,21,"and neglect the Hereafter.",""
  75,22,"On that Day some faces will be bright,",""
  75,23,"looking at their Lord<sup>7</sup>.","[7] The dwellers of Paradise will be granted the honor of actually seeing their Lord in the Hereafter."
  75,24,"And on that Day, some faces will be gloomy,",""
  75,25,"knowing that a crushing calamity will befall them.",""
  75,26,"Indeed, when the soul reaches the throat<sup>8</sup>,","[8] Upon death."
  75,27,"and it is said, “Is there any healer?”",""
  75,28,"And he realizes that it is time to depart,",""
  75,29,"when legs are brought together [in a shroud]<sup>9</sup>;","[9] The difficulties the person faces while leaving this world and moving on to the Hereafter; or the people arrange for the departure of his body, while angels arrange for the departure of his soul."
  75,30,"on that Day, he will be driven to your Lord.",""
  75,31,"He neither believed nor prayed;",""
  75,32,"rather he denied and turned away,",""
  75,33,"then he went to his people, elated with pride,",""
  75,34,"Woe to you, and woe!",""
  75,35,"Again, woe to you, and woe!",""
  75,36,"Does man think that he will be left neglected<sup>10</sup>?","[10] i.e., without purpose and responsibility, or without returning to Allah for account."
  75,37,"Was he not once a drop of semen emitted,",""
  75,38,"then he became a clinging clot<sup>11</sup>, then He created him and perfected his form,","[11] ""‘Alaqah"": an embryo that resembles a leech."
  75,39,"and made from him both genders, male and female?",""
  75,40,"Is not He able to bring the dead back to life?",""
  76,1,"Was there not a period of time when man was not a thing [even] mentioned<sup>1</sup>?","[1] Before coming into being."
  76,2,"Indeed, We created man from a drop of mixed fluids<sup>2</sup>, in order to test him. So We gave him hearing and sight.","[2] A combination of male and female gametes (sperm and egg) which form the zygote after fertilization in the womb."
  76,3,"Indeed, We showed him the way, whether he is grateful or ungrateful.",""
  76,4,"We have surely prepared for the disbelievers chains, shackles, and a Blazing Fire.",""
  76,5,"Indeed, the righteous will drink from a cup [of wine] flavored with camphor<sup>3</sup>,","[3] ""Kāfoor"": a sweet-scent spring in Paradise."
